llenge%20flyer%22%20title%3D%22Trivia%20Challenge%20%2F%20Trivia%20Madness%20flyer%2C%20%C2%A91985%20M.%20Kramer%20Manufacturing%2C%20image%20via%20The%20Arcade%20Flyer%20Archive%20(sister%20cabinet%20on%20the%20same%20Kramer%20board)%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20id%3D%22the-cabinet%22%3EThe%20Cabinet%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrivia%20Madness%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Csup%20id%3D%22fnref%3A1%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22%23fn%3A1%22%20class%3D%22footnote-ref%22%20role%3D%22doc-noteref%22%3E1%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fsup%3E%20shipped%20in%201985%20from%20Thunderhead%20Inc.%2C%20built%20on%20a%0Acountertop%20board%20designed%20by%20M.%20Kramer%20Manufacturing%20of%20Asbury%20Park%2C%20NJ.%0AKramer%20was%20a%20tiny%20player%20in%20the%20bar-trivia%20boom%2C%20their%20catalog%20totals%0Aonly%20two%20known%20cabinets%2C%20the%20other%20being%20the%20almost-impossible-to-find%0A%3Cstrong%3ELA%20Beer%20Trivia%20Challenge%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20an%20Anheuser-Busch-licensed%20machine%20that%0Adebuted%20at%20the%201985%20AMOA%20Expo.%20Both%20run%20the%20same%20basic%20hardware.%20The%0Atrivia%20was%20the%20product%3B%20the%20Kramer%20board%20was%20the%20delivery%20vehicle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%20Trivia%20Madness%20was%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnever%20dumped%E2%80%9D%20list%20at%0A%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fmaws.mameworld.info%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%20rel%3D%22noopener%22%3Emameworld.info%2Fmaws%3C%2Fa%3E%0A.%20The%20cabinet%20was%20rare%0Aenough%2C%20and%20Kramer%20obscure%20enough%2C%20that%20nobody%20with%20an%20EPROM%20reader%20had%0Aever%20pulled%20its%20chips%2C%20until%20May%202021%2C%20when%20an%20uploader%20called%20%E2%80%9CSketch%0Athe%20Cow%E2%80%9D%20dropped%20a%20complete%20dump%20onto%20the%20Internet%20Archive%20as%0A%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Farcade_trvmadns%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%20rel%3D%22noopener%22%3E%3Ccode%3Earcade_trvmadns%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%0A.%0APlayable%20in%20a%20browser%20immediately.%20Extractable%2C%20with%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20id%3D%22the-data%22%3EThe%20Data%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAll%203%2C790%20records%20browse%20at%0A%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fquiz.toys%2Farchive%2Fbrowse%3Fsource%3Dkramer_trvmadns%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%20rel%3D%22noopener%22%3E%2Fbrowse%3Fsource%3Dkramer_trvmadns%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%0Aa%20mix%20of%20True%2FFalse%20(2%2C124)%20and%20Multiple-Choice%20(1%2C666)%20questions%0Aacross%20eight%20category%20chips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EExtractor%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Ftholman%2Fquiz-toys%2Fblob%2Fmain%2Fscripts%2Fthunderhead%2Fextract.py%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%20rel%3D%22noopener%22%3E%3Ccode%3Escripts%2Fthunderhead%2Fextract.py%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOriginal%20ROM%20dump%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Farcade_trvmadns%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%20rel%3D%22noopener%22%3Earchive.org%2Fdetails%2Farcade_trvmadns%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMAMEWorld%20unMAMEd%20entry%20(historical)%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Funmamed.mameworld.info%2Fnon_other80.html%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%20rel%3D%22noopener%22%3Enon_other80.html%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20id%3D%22how-we-cracked-it%22%3EHow%20We%20Cracked%20It%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%20id%3D%22the-hook-two-formats-one-cabinet%22%3EThe%20Hook%3A%20Two%20Formats%2C%20One%20Cabinet%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trivia%20Madness%20board%20accepts%20question%20ROM%20chips%20in%20any%20of%2016%20bank%0Apositions.%20Operators%20could%20mix-and-match%20chips%20across%20categories.%20Most%0Abar-top%20trivia%20cabinets%20of%20this%20era%20use%20one%20format%3B%20Kramer%20used%20two%2C%0Adepending%20on%20the%20category%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrue%2FFalse%20chips%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20(sex%2C%20soaps%2C%20rebel%2C%20star%20trek)%20store%20short%0Astatements%20followed%20by%20%3Ccode%3E.*T%3C%2Fcode%3E%20or%20%3Ccode%3E.*F%3C%2Fcode%3E.%20Players%20answer%20TRUE%20or%20FALSE.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EMultiple-Choice%20chips%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20(entertainment%2C%20sports%2C%20TV%2C%20travel)%20store%0Afour-option%20records%3A%20%3Ccode%3E%5C%26lt%3Bquestion%26gt%3B*%26lt%3Bcorrect%26gt%3B*%26lt%3Bwrong1%26gt%3B*%26lt%3Bwrong2%26gt%3B*%3C%2Fcode%3E.%0APlayers%20pick%20A%2C%20B%2C%20or%20C.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESame%20cabinet%2C%20same%20Z80%2C%20same%20ROM%20socket%2C%20the%20game%20code%20dispatches%20on%0Aa%20marker%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20chip%20(%E2%80%9CMC%E2%80%9D%20for%20multiple-choice%2C%20a%20plain%0A%3Ccode%3E%5C%3C%2Fcode%3E%20for%20True%2FFalse).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20id%3D%22the-truefalse-format%22%3EThe%20True%2FFalse%20Format%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETF%20chips%20have%20no%20header.%20Records%20run%20top-to-bottom%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cpre%20tabindex%3D%220%22%3E%3Ccode%3E%5CSEXUAL%20ACTIVITY%20ELICITS%26lt%3BHORMONAL%20RESPONSES.*T%0A%5CA%20WOMAN%20CANNOT%20RAPE%26lt%3BA%20MAN.*F%0A%5CTHE%20CLITORIS%20HAS%20OTHER%26lt%3BPURPOSES%20BESIDES%26lt%3BPROVIDING%20PLEASURE.*F%0A%5CKAI%20TEK%20AIRPORT%26lt%3BIS%20IN%20CHINA.*T%0A%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fpre%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ccode%3E%5C%3C%2Fcode%3E%20marks%20the%20start%20of%20a%20record.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ccode%3E%26lt%3B%3C%2Fcode%3E%20is%20a%20display%20line%20break%2C%20the%20monitor%20wrapped%20text%20at%20fixed%0Acharacter%20positions%20and%20the%20designers%20pre-computed%20where%20to%20break.%0AStripped%20to%20a%20space%20on%20extract.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ccode%3E.*T%3C%2Fcode%3E%20or%20%3Ccode%3E.*F%3C%2Fcode%3E%20terminates%20the%20record%20with%20the%20answer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBytes%20in%20the%20%3Ccode%3E0x80-0xFF%3C%2Fcode%3E%20range%20inside%20a%20TF%20chip%20are%20inline%20word%20tokens.%0AUnlike%20the%20MC%20chips%2C%20TF%20chips%20carry%20no%20dictionary%20of%20their%20own%2C%20the%0AZ80%20dispatches%20through%20a%20board-wide%20phrase%20table%20baked%20into%20one%20of%0Athe%20program%20ROMs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20id%3D%22finding-the-tf-dictionary%22%3EFinding%20the%20TF%20Dictionary%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20initial%20pass%20at%20the%20TF%20chips%20left%20every%20question%20peppered%20with%0Ahigh-bit%20bytes%20that%20we%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20expand.%20The%20dictionary%20had%20to%20exist%0Asomewhere%2C%20the%20cabinet%20obviously%20renders%20full%20English%20on%20screen.%0Abut%20program%20ROM%20%3Ccode%3Eu5%3C%2Fcode%3E%20(the%20main%20Z80%20code)%20held%20only%20code%2C%20strings%2C%0Aand%20the%20attract-mode%20text.%20We%20almost%20shipped%20with%20the%20TF%20tokens%0Astripped%20and%20moved%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fix%20was%20to%20scan%20%3Cem%3Eevery%3C%2Fem%3E%20ROM%20on%20the%20board%20for%20a%20specific%0Astructural%20signature%3A%20a%20byte%20sequence%20where%20a%20high-bit%20token%20byte%0A(0x80%2C%200x81%2C%200x82%E2%80%A6)%20is%20followed%20by%20a%20short%20ASCII%20phrase%2C%20which%20is%0Afollowed%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3Enext%3C%2Fem%3E%20sequential%20token%20byte%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20The%20pattern%0Alands%20on%20a%20real%20dictionary%20and%20ignores%20incidental%20ASCII%20runs.%20Exactly%0Aone%20hit%20across%2040%20KB%20of%20ROM%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3Eu6%20%E2%80%9Cgreen%E2%80%9D%20at%20offset%200x1EC0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20a%2049-entry%20phrase%20table%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cpre%20tabindex%3D%220%22%3E%3Ccode%3E%20%200x80%20WHO%20%20%200x81%20WHERE%20%200x82%20WHAT%20%200x83%20WHEN%20%200x84%20HOW%0A%20%200x85%20WAS%20%20%200x86%20THE%20%20%20%200x87%20IN%20%20%20%200x88%20OF%20%20%20%200x89%20IS%0A%20%200x8A%20AS%20%20%20%200x8B%20AN%20%20%20%20%200x8C%20WHICH%200x8D%20AND%20%20%200x8E%20HAD%0A%20%200x8F%20TO%20%20%20%200x90%20ON%20%20%20%20%200x91%20ARE%20%20%200x92%20DID%20%20%200x93%20FOR%0A%20%200x94%20HAVE%20%200x95%20WITH%20%20%200x96%20FROM%20%200x97%20YOU%20%20%200x98%20SPENDING%0A%20%200x99%20WHO%20WAS%20THE%20%20%20%20%20%20%200x9A%20WHEN%20WAS%20THE%0A%20%200x9B%20HOW%20MANY%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%200x9C%2019%20%20%200x9D%20LEAD%0A%20%200x9E%20WHERE%20WAS%20THE%20%20%20%20%200x9F%20WAS%20THE%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%200xA0%20MOST%0A%20%200xA1%20YEAR%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%200xA2%20HIGHEST%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%200xA3%20THAT%0A%20%200xA4%20TIME%200xA5%20ONLY%20%20%20%200xA6%20I%20SAY%20LA%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%200xA7%20I%20SAY%20LA%20WHEN%0A%20%200xA8%20AT%20%20%200xA9%20I'VE%20%20%20%200xAA%20GOT%20%20%200xAB%20I'M%20%20%200xAC%20LONG%0A%20%200xAD%20IT'S%200xAE%20DAY%20%20%20%20%200xAF%20WORK%20%200xB0%20PARTY%0A%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fpre%3E%3Cp%3Eu6%20is%20labelled%20%E2%80%9Cgreen%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20board%2C%20ostensibly%20the%20green%20colour%0Aplane%20of%20the%20character%20ROM%2C%20but%20Kramer%20quietly%20parked%20the%20dictionary%0Ain%20the%20tail%20of%20the%20file%20where%20the%20graphics%20would%20otherwise%20be%20all%0A0xFF%20padding.%20%3Cem%3EThat%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20why%20the%20earlier%20pass%20missed%20it%3A%20nobody%20looks%0Afor%20phrase%20tables%20inside%20a%20colour%20ROM.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20dict%20applied%2C%20TF%20questions%20read%20as%20full%20English.%20Byte%20%3Ccode%3E0x86%3C%2Fcode%3E%0Aalone%20(the%20most%20common%20token%2C%202%2C125%20occurrences)%20is%20%E2%80%9CTHE%E2%80%9D%2C%20two%0Athousand%20missing%20THEs.%20The%20MC%20chips%20layer%20their%20per-chip%200xC0%2B%0Adictionary%20on%20top%20of%20the%20same%20board-wide%20table%2C%20so%20words%20like%20%E2%80%9CWHO%0AWAS%20THE%E2%80%9D%20get%20a%20token%20in%20the%20global%20table%20and%20chip-specific%20entries%0Alike%20%E2%80%9CALL%20MY%20CHILDREN%E2%80%9D%20get%20a%20token%20in%20the%20per-chip%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20~130%20high-bit%20bytes%20in%20the%200xB1-0xEF%20range%20remain%20unmapped.%0Aper-chip%20category%20tokens%20(things%20like%20%E2%80%9CSEXUAL%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CONCE%20MARRIED%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CSOAP%0AOPERA%E2%80%9D)%20we%20haven%E2%80%99t%20located%20a%20storage%20site%20for.%20Those%20are%20silently%0Adropped%20during%20extraction%20rather%20than%20rendered%20as%20placeholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20id%3D%22the-multiple-choice-format%22%3EThe%20Multiple-Choice%20Format%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMC%20chips%20carry%20their%20own%20per-chip%20phrase%20dictionary.%20The%20layout%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cpre%20tabindex%3D%220%22%3E%3Ccode%3E%20%200x0000%20%20%20%20%22MC%22%20magic%0A%20%200x0004%20%20%20%20category%20name%20%2B%20%22*%22%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%200xFF%20padding%20(~250%20bytes)%0A%20%200x0100%20%20%20%20Token%20dictionary%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20-%20Each%20token%20entry%20is%20%26lt%3Bbyte%200xC0-0xFE%26gt%3B%26lt%3BASCII%20text%26gt%3B%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20-%20Runs%20until%20the%20next%200xC0-0xFE%20byte%20or%200xFF%20padding%0A%20%20~0x0380%20%20%200xFF%20padding%0A%20%20~0x0400%20%20%20Records%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%5C%26lt%3Bquestion%26gt%3B*%26lt%3Bcorrect%26gt%3B*%26lt%3Bwrong1%26gt%3B*%26lt%3Bwrong2%26gt%3B*%0A%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fpre%3E%3Cp%3EReading%20the%20Entertainment%20chip%E2%80%99s%20dictionary%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cpre%20tabindex%3D%220%22%3E%3Ccode%3E%20%200xC0%3A%20'PLAYED%20THE%20TITLE%20ROLE'%0A%20%200xC1%3A%20'WHO%20RECORDED%20THE%20THEME%20SONG'%0A%20%200xC2%3A%20'%20BALLAD'%0A%20%200xC4%3A%20'%5Cx86%5Cx9c53'%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%E2%86%90%20garbage%20(chained%20to%20another%20token)%0A%20%200xC5%3A%20'LORRETTA%20LYNN*%5Cx82%5Cx85%20CHARLIE%20CHAPLIN%5C'S%26lt%3B'%0A%20%200xC7%3A%20'CHARLES%20BRONSON'%0A%20%200xC8%3A%20'DUSTIN%20HOFFMAN'%0A%20%200xC9%3A%20'BURT%20LANCASTER'%0A%20%200xCA%3A%20'JACK%20NICHOLSON'%0A%20%200xCB%3A%20'CLINT%20EASTWOOD'%0A%20%200xCC%3A%20'WHAT%20ACTOR%20PLAYED'%0A%20%20...%0A%20%200xE4%3A%20'JAMES'%0A%20%200xE5%3A%20'FIRST'%0A%20%200xE6%3A%20'OSCAR'%0A%20%200xE7%3A%20'JACK'%0A%20%200xE8%3A%20'JOHN'%0A%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fpre%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20chip%20defines%20roughly%2050%20tokens%2C%20mostly%20actor%20names%2C%20common%0Afilm%2Fmusic%20vocabulary%2C%20and%20short%20connectives.%20Each%20category%20has%20its%0Aown%20vocabulary%20because%20the%20space%20savings%20are%20category-specific%3A%0Asports%20chips%20define%20%E2%80%9CTOUCHDOWN%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CQUARTERBACK%E2%80%9D%2C%20team%20names%3B%20travel%0Achips%20define%20%E2%80%9CCAPITAL%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9COCEAN%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CCONTINENT%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20token%20expansion%2C%20a%20record%20reads%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cpre%20tabindex%3D%220%22%3E%3Ccode%3E%5CWHO%20CO-STARRED%20WITH%20ELVIS%20IN%20THE%20MOVIE%2C%20%22VIVA%20LAS%20VEGAS%22%0A%20%20%20%20*ANN-MARGRET*LANA%20TURNER*RITA%20HAYWORTH*%0A%3C%2Fcode%3E%3C%2Fpre%3E%3Cp%3ECorrect%20answer%20is%20always%20the%20first%20field%20after%20the%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20id%3D%22what-tripped-us-up%22%3EWhat%20Tripped%20Us%20Up%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20false%20starts%20before%20the%20real%20solve%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMis-identifying%20the%20MC%20dictionary.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20records%20themselves%20contain%0Abytes%20in%20the%200xC0-0xFE%20range%20(from%20token%20references)%2C%20so%20a%20naive%0Adict-scanner%20that%20looks%20for%20%E2%80%9Cconsecutive%200xC0%2B%20bytes%E2%80%9D%20will%20latch%20onto%0Athe%20%3Cem%3Erecord%3C%2Fem%3E%20section%20instead%20of%20the%20real%20dictionary.%20The%20fix%20was%20to%0Afind%20the%20%3Cstrong%3Efirst%3C%2Fstrong%3E%200xC0%20in%20the%20file%2C%20because%20the%20dictionary%20always%0Asits%20before%20the%20records%2C%20the%20first%20occurrence%20is%20always%20the%20real%0Adictionary%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELooking%20in%20the%20wrong%20ROM%20for%20the%20TF%20table.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20first%20pass%20searched%0Au5%20(the%20main%20Z80%20code)%20and%20u7%20(graphics)%20for%20a%20phrase%20table%2C%20nothing%0Athere.%20The%20table%20lives%20in%20u6%20(%E2%80%9Cgreen%E2%80%9D%20colour%20ROM)%2C%20which%20no%20one%0Anormally%20scans%20for%20text.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETreating%20TF%20chips%20as%20%E2%80%9Cdictionary-less%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20second%20pass%20just%0Astripped%20all%20high-bit%20bytes%20from%20TF%20records%20rather%20than%20expand%20them%2C%0Aproducing%20r